explanation:
- OS_FileSys_Initialize: OS_initfs calls this function directly; any use of memcmp on the devname/volname parameters (or other null-terminated strings) will be inside this routine, so its implementation is required to determine a MISRA memcmp violation.  
- OS_FileSysStartVolume_Impl, OS_FileSysFormatVolume_Impl, OS_FileSysStopVolume_Impl: these are callees of OS_FileSys_Initialize (per the call graph) and are likely places where device/volume names are compared. Their implementations must be inspected to find indirect uses of memcmp on null-terminated strings.  
- memcmp: the standard-library function itself must be located/inspected to identify calls to it (direct or indirect) and to check how its arguments are constructed (e.g., whether it is being used on null-terminated C-strings rather than on binary buffers).
